76561197970632001,Recommended,220200,29985910,Posted: 17 February,all,Sangmin,"It's okay for a couple hours.*Update*So, all jokes aside, I felt like it would be good to give this review a little more effort to make it more useful for people considering the game.This is a game I wouldn't hesitate to recommend to anyone who has interest in space or exploration. You will learn how NASA and other space agencies perform maneuvers such as orbital rendezvous and Hohmann transfer orbits. Unlike some games that have been claimed to ""have potential"", this is a game where you discover YOUR OWN potential for planning and finding creative ways to accomplish tasks.Vehicle construction works like Legos and is very intuitive. The modding community is HUGE and there are lots of tools that make designing the perfect vehicle easier, such as delta v and thrust to weight ratio calculations. This sounds educational, and it is, but it is incredibly fun and gives an immense sense of accomplishment when you learn how to reach your next milestone. The feeling of landing on another celestial body the first time is an unparalleled sense of satisfaction.This is Early Access done right. The game is fantastic and has infinite replayability. This is the most bang (literally) for your buck you will get out of any game.In the words of Scott Manley, ""Fly safe."""
