76561197971724802,Recommended,220200,25004535,"Posted: 18 August, 2016",all,Pontifex Maximus,"Kerbal Space Programis a deceptively dense game hiding behind the cute green Kerbals that populate this space-age world. In Career mode you’re given a basic NASA-like facility. Buildings include Vehicle Assembly, Tracking Station, Mission Control, and a launch site that’s little more than a slab of concrete.Money is earned by accepting various missions, such as providing an orbital touring service, testing out new engine parts, and reaching the Mun. You can earn Science credits by succeeding in missions and using certain devices. Science is spent on a tech tree that unlocks advanced parts and components.A bunch of scenarios provide interesting challenges to work through, like returning a Kerbal from the Mun safely. There’s a ton of gameplay and replay value packed in.The heart ofKerbal Space Programlies in the Vehicle Assembly Building. The builder is intuitive and fun to snap together. You need to take heed of where all your parts go, and how your ship will steer. Decouplers eliminate empty engines and spare parts. Engines can be tweaked to carry a certain amount of fuel. Each device is activated through a staging sequence by pressing the spacebar before and during flight.Kerbal Space Programisrocket science. While the learning curve is rather steep, what the game sets out to do, it does extremely well.THE GOOD- Limitless creative freedom- Well designed, challenging career mode- Unbelievably impressive attention to detail- Incredible sense of satisfaction- Rewards persistence- Kerbals are hilariousTHE BAD- Mass amounts of information- A bit overwhelming at times- Default text size too small- Various camera modes can lead to nausea- A few graphical glitches9/10DISASTER | BAD | MEDIOCRE | OKAY | GOOD | GREAT |AMAZING| MASTERPIECE"
