,Recommended,220200,9216272,"Posted: 22 February, 2014",all,LionsPhil,"This is:- how to do edutainment- a demonstration of the power of adding a little personality to an otherwise dry and difficult challenge, making failure hilarious instead, and success all that sweeter- sufficiently gameified that you can get to the moon-analogue and back using a wobbly stack of exploding things, steering with WASD, and do it within a few hours rather than years of meticulous planning and precision engineering- sufficiently accurate in the broad strokes that you can get a really good gut understanding of rocket science and orbital mechanics, and one of the most notable Lets Play-ers (Scott Manley) has a couple of physics and astronomy degrees- absolutely thriving with mods to push it further into either direction if you so desire (and as a pure utility, Kerbal Alarm Clock is excellent for managing scaling up to multiple concurrent interplanetary missions)- far, far more rewarding than a ""level up!"" screen when you set yourself a dot in the sky to visit, and finally make it there and back intact- an early access game which is worth the (inevitable sale) money for what's already been made (writing this as of version 0.23), not some nebulous future potential- why I have not had any ""free time"" for the past month- JEBEDIAH KERMAN, THRILLMASTER"
