,Recommended,220200,22107450,"Posted: 28 March, 2016",all,bagelsmith,"The best simulation game I've ever played! The stock game is amazing enough for trying to get to orbit, and other planets (very hard, still havent landed everywhere in one trip.. after 1000 hours). Also boats and land vehicles if you're into that (on other planets too why not?). But with mods... it can become every other sim game youve ever wanted! And a handy community run mod database and manager (CKAN) to make it easy!Flight combat sim: install realistic aerodynamic mod and weapons mod to make your own F15s fight your own Su-27s (FAR and BDarmory).Colony building: there are life support and resource collecting mods that challenge you to scan for the right site and use resources on any of the planets to sustain a colony of kerbals; even manufacture new parts there (MKS, TAC lifesupport, extraplanetary launchpads, scansat, remotetech).Hardcore realistic simulation? Theres a mod that converts the stock star system to a 1:1 scale replica of the solar system, with real-life satellite data used (real solar system, realism overhaul, probably more mods - these are too scary for me). Realism overhaul I think uses historical rocket data so you can create saturn-V replicas with the accurate fuel mixtures and everything!Or go the other way and get futuristic mods to create antimatter powered near-light speed craft to visit entire other solar systems (nearfuture, KSPinterstellar)!And with the new 1.1 release on Unity 5, you may actually be able to use these mods without running out of memory!Between the great modding community and active devs (for over 5 years!) this game will continue to get better and better, so even at full price of $40 its a great deal!"
