,Recommended,220200,22014857,"Posted: 23 March, 2016",all,fizilicious,"An excellent space simulation game with tons of user-made contents and mods existed. Learning curve is quite steep, but once you understand it the experience is priceless. Some of the features are much simplified from real life rocket science due to technical and gameplay reasons (no n-body physics, less punishing air resistance model, etc), yet it is still quite challenging for beginners (including me lol).While the vanilla version of the game is already almost perfect, it is greatly improved by the mod supports. There are tons of contents and mods in the repository, like adding a far more realistic physics (better air resistance model, realistic planet size, experimental n-body system), adding sci-fi and far-future engines (like Alcubierre warp drive and wormholes),  adding new robot parts (yes, you can build Macross' Valkyrie and Gundam) and adding a whole new exoplanet system. Heck, there are even programming mods if you want to challenge yourself to fly your own space ships just by code!So, in Kerbal Space Program, the sky is not the limit."
