76561197971872842,Recommended,220200,13144502,"Posted: 29 November, 2014",all,Riph,"Pros:+Totally open ended, build whatever sort of rockets you like.+Persistent universe, rockets you send up today can serve as docking platforms or refueling stations for things you send tomorrow.+Fun cartoon aesthetic.+Built-in procedural quest system (Contracts) always available to give you new goals.  They're totally optional, you can fly wherever your fuel will take you.+This game taught me orbital mechanics.Cons:-Rough optimization.  You may need a beefy rig especially if you want to make big complicated rockets.  However a small rocket can complete most of the in game challenges and is kinder on your system.-Control scheme can take some getting used to.  Everything is rebindable though.-Dedication to realism means that you're sometimes hitting the time compression button and waiting (and waiting) for an orbital launch window to open.  However this is only an issue for distant planets.  The moon is always nearby and ready to explore.This game doesn't hold your hand because there's not one (or even ten) correct answers to any problem.  You may find certain tasks like getting a stable orbit or docking with another craft challenging, but there's literally hundreds of cheerful, informative youtube vids offering tips.  And if it starts hard, you'll feel like a boss when you finally nail it."
