,Recommended,220200,7746231,"Posted: 25 November, 2013",all,Colditz Colligula,"Mun or bust!  Put those solid fuel boosters on that capsule and send mastermind Jebediah Kerman on a trip to.. whatever it is you hit in space!In Kerbal Space Program you're put in charge of a Space Center run by Kerbals, the inhabitants of Kerbin, a race so eager to explore space they'd put rockets on everything.Your job is to build Rockets, Rovers, Space-Planes.. yes, even Space Stations and launch them into Space to explore/ fly-around-in and land (or crash) into and onto Moons, Planets and even Asteroids and build your scientific base there.There's really only one downside, and that's an incredibly steep learning curve. Thanks to an incredible amount of Video and Written Tutorials on the Web, especially Youtube, you're get a hang of it in due time. The game also comes with a few basic tutorials on how to build a ship and maneuvering it in space.It takes a bit of scientific knowledge to understand how moving in space works. Kerbal Space Program (KSP) often refers to scientific terms for things and is proud of itself as being a very realistic presentation of how Space works.If you can get past your early crashes and misbuilt ships, what lies ahead of you is a journey to the stars with your own crew of Kerbals, in your very own Ship towards a Planet you're going to put your flag on.The Game offers a Campaign and a Sandbox mode. In Sandbox you can pretty much do whatever the heck you want. Build a Ship out of infinite materials and try launching it into space, or better, try landing it somewhere. In the Carreer Mode of the Game you need to start with baby steps. Perform some easy things like orbiting, collecting Scientific Data along the way and hiring new Astronauts to help you in your quest for the Stars and gaining new Materials. Slowly explore Space and the many things it has to offer.With lots of user created mods and community created overhauls for Sounds and Textures and a generally booming Modding Community that is also being appreciated and even incorporated into the Games releases you'll never run out of new Materials for building your dream-ship.Now go and conquer those Stars.4.5/5"
