76561197970440937,Recommended,220200,8053453,"Posted: 15 December, 2013",all,Eldritch Crank,"Kerbal Space Program is one of my ""Games of the Generation"" for whatever that may be worth (the other one is a certain game with Souls that are Dark...you know.)I will skip what KSP is, to make it short, a Space Program Simulator. You build Spacecraft like Rockets, Landers and Rovers and try to get them to other celestial bodies in the simulation...or you can mess around with your creations and create huge deadly fireworks, that works too ;)What makes KSP so special to me is the sense of achievement it conveys when you finally get something right. Let me make this clear right away, KSP is not a simple or easy game. Your first hours will consist of hillarious failiure (if you don´t consult any guides).But once you get your first stable orbit, it feels like you really achieved something, which you did, getting a functional spacecraft in orbit is NOT easy for a beginner. And it only gets more complex AND awesome from there. In Sandbox-Mode, you have no goals beside the ones you set for yourself. Want to go to the furthes planet and set up a network of probes there? You can do it...if you can do it ;)KSP consists of two main modes while you play: Building your vessels and then launching and controlling them. The cool thing is, KSP is not only fun, it also teaches you some things about Astrophysics, even if the physics here are simplified.Bottom Line:If you like thinkey, slowpaced games that let you build and lead your creations to success, if you AT ALL like Space and the wonderful endeavour that is traveling to other celestial bodies, careful maneauvering and putting your very own flag down on the moon (you can totally do that btw), you HAVE to play Kerbal Space Program, one of the most ambitious, brave and rewarding games about space you will ever play.One final word about Early Access: KSP is in development, yes, but it already offers SO much content and possibilites, let alone Mods for just about anything, that I can see no reason not to jump on the KSP-train right now. The sooner you get it, the sooner you will feel that satisfaction when the blue sky fades, the stars shining brightly above your small vessel while the sound of your rocket slowly gets quieter, only to be replaced by the serene soundtrack and a feeling of awe when you´re confronted with space....you can probably tell how much I like this game ;)"
