,Recommended,220200,987586,"Posted: 11 August, 2013",all,Mithadon,"10/10Kerbal Space Program just might be the game of my life! For someone who is passionate about space exploration, there is simply nothing that even comes close. An enormous sandbox in which you can plan and design your own missions. However ambitious you're feeling, you can think of a mission that will REALLY challenge you. And when you finally reach the goal you had set for yourself, you will feel a tremendous sense of pride and accomplishment. This game can be exquisitely complex, which definitely makes it a niche title - but it's really what makes it so good. My biggest mission to date took me 16 hours, of which roughly 10 were spent designing my gigantic rocket. I like to use real formulae for thrust to weight, planetary transfers, terminal velocity, etc. and plan the entire mission before leaving ground, and not use auto-pilot (mechjeb is what most people use and it can be incredibly helpful). I'm a masochist like that. This game is so good that I try not to play, or else I cannot stop and will not go to bed ever.Even in early access, this game has everything it needs. Make sure you google and search through the numerous mods, which can increase realism and add many features (comm networks, planetary scanning, mining operations, GPS, telescopes, enhanced aerodynamics, to name just a few).Simply incredible."
