,Recommended,220200,8600785,"Posted: 6 January, 2014",all,BSoD,"Best Game Ever!.. In my opinion anyway ;)If you have a background of interest in sandbox and/or simulator games you're sure to get your money's worth of enjoyment out of Kerbal Space Program.The game is renowned for having a truly Everest like learning curve. So if you're a type to be frustrated when things don't work first time round beware.However, at this point the game has a nice set of tutorials to get you going on the basics and some clearly thought out scenarios which you can use to drop you in situations to practice most other things (without going to the trouble of getting those pesky rockets off the launch pad).I have found the game to be relatively low on bugs at this point (although rockets do have a tendency to fall apart on the launch pad sometimes). But as the game is still early access it's safe to assume these will be fixed with time.Overall Kerbal is a Great Game. Lots of depth for those willing to put in the time and the promise of comical failures and explosions for all!"
