76561197980207889,Recommended,220200,24826035,"Posted: 11 August, 2016",all,[MAD] Mechanicus,"KSP is a physics game which means its not for everyone. It is somewhat technical but thanks to its cartoonish approach funny at the same time.You build your rocket or your plane in the hangar, go to the launchpad/runway and watch it fly ( or die trying ).The graphics are pretty basic but that has no negative impact on the game for me (i for one prefer a good game to good looks).It can be somewhat repetitive. You're going to repeat ALOT of your flights until they yield the results you set out for but with the tinkering in between trying to optimize your design its okay for me.There are 3 gameplay-modes to choose from.1) Sandbox: just build what you want and let it fly.2) Science: Get scientific data from different locations to advance your rockets like various climate zones of your own planet, in flight, in orbit, heck even swimming in the ocean and in space of course. Just worry about the data no matter the costs.3) Career: You pretty much run the whole show yourself if its science/piloting/managing/work on contracts etc.For me it was totally worth it and im not done yet. :D"
