76561198082123142,Recommended,220200,7939806,"Posted: 6 December, 2013",all,xico,"Just a fantastic game that has shown to be able to catch the attention of gamers from many different genres. I love my fighting games too, but it's refreshing to build rockets and space planes without considering weaponry or militarism of any kind. This is a journey of discovery, where you build on the knowledge from previous trips off-world.The expansiveness of this game, when it's not even yet in beta, is impressive to say the least. To give an example, below is a list of projects each of my friends are endeavoring currently:-Building a fueling station in orbit of Kerbal (the Earth-like planet)-Building a rover to fly to the moon and recover two stranded astronauts from a botched landing-Space planes are so cool!-And in the name of science I am trying to build an unmanned vessel that will be sent into the sun.Because each these activities provide different pieces of information, you accumulate science points for further tech development.This all said, the game is unfinished so while there is a tremendous amount that can be done, if you are the type of gamer that wants things streamlined then I would recommend waiting for the official release.I'm always fond of developers that put out demos! It's generally a good indicator of a game they feel speaks for itself._________Now summer 2015, with the game being released I have to say the game is left much to be desired. I love this game, and will continue to play it but I am disappointed at how the devs (despite a massive influx of financing) didn't follow through with the admittedly vast scope of this game. It would have been nice to have cities on Kerbin so the planet feels inhabited, along with far more points of research.With science being an important aspect to the game's economy I had hoped for slightly more detail for those interested like spectrometers and chromatograhs of samples and scanners of celestial bodies. Rather than grind to reach various locations on moons and planets give specific locations potential importance. Like presence of ice to be used for habitability of grounded stations or used for fuel. What happened to movement IVA like in the initial trailers?It felt in the months after the purchase of the dev company  by the big boys the game was rushed to completion. Some marketing fuddy figured making dolls and knick knacks is a quicker turn around than a finished game.Because the game is easily moddable however, at least the legacy will be left for those who put in the time for the love of the game.Still amazing game, who doesn't want to design, build, and operate rockets, landers, rovers, space planes, probes, and stations off-world?"
