,Recommended,220200,13464805,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,✈ Alex,"My name is Alex the Airplane andI LOVE THIS GAMELook at those cute Kerbals! Their expression of utter confusion and dread as your mistake careens towards the VAB always breaks my heart. ):How do you even begin to describe this work of art(Endorsed by NASA!), as compared to mainstream blockbusters designed to milk every cent out of your pocket with limited release content and outrageously hollow but aggressively priced DLCs? They've done so much to improve the game from just a few ugly parts to this masterpiece complete with Contracts, mission, and Science, intergrating wonderful community mods and even modders into their great project, bac9 you are a good man.You can play the base game and learn the basics of orbital mechanics, fuel conservation, delta V calculations and how wonderful it is to hear that serene music playing as you finally take the first step into the unforgiving void. Or you can open the pandora's box and install mods, add new tech likeInterstellar, challenge yourself with accurate(as possible) aerodynamics with FAR, be a masochist with reentry heat modeling on DeadlyReentry, make it hyper realistic from planet size to atmosphere depth to engine efficiency with Realism Overhaul. Break the taboo and turn what was meant to create, conserve, advance, and enrich kerbalkind into something moresinister, you evil man you! If fantasy is your cup of tea, why not fly USS Enterprise past the sun? The community is filled with kindhearted and intelligent members, sharing and caring for eachother, can't go wrong with that!Playing this game your way is the theme here, do you want to meticulously plan a fleet mission to the Jool system and nab every science points you can while also establishing a permanent colony? Or just build silly things to fly around KSC? Invent new ways to use parts like combining landing gears, fuel tanks, and wings to create working stock helicopters or build your dream SSTO with the help of a little part stat modding(Cheat away, no one will judge you!) Recreations of popular media likeA Jaeger maybe?You know this game will be worth your time when you have thesetalentedandartisticpeople creating contents worthy of hours of enjoyment. That's what it means to be cinematic, not some 30 frames per second nonsense. You'll only be hitting those frames because your partcount is too high, not when there's too many NPCs on screen.What I've mentioned just scratches the surface of this jewel, every moment of your time spent will be filled with meaning. The times when you first attempt an orbital rendezvous(probably fail like NASA did their first time) and that sense of euphoric accomplishment after completing your dyson sphere colony, or maybe when you've barely squeezed enough dV to make the course back to Kerbin after getting out and pushing your spacecraft with your jetpack.You may not be like me, but this holiday season, don't buy Battle of Duty: Destiny of a Titan, spend the money on this earnest product of science, maybe donate some to the great mod developers, send the rest to a charity(Maybe even Greenpeace, if you're okay with the fact that they've vandalized the Nazca lines)."
