,Recommended,220200,9098047,"Posted: 13 February, 2014",all,mike013,"As others have said before this is a terrific sandbox game, that lets you play nasa and lets you do anything you want within the limits of the laws of physics.You can just have a good laugh shooting kerbals into suborbit and letting them crash down or you can approach it scientific by orbiting compleet bases like the iss or refueling bases. You can then launch a two step rocket: first into orbit and dock at your previously launched station, refuel there and then continu your journey to other planets in the solar system.Also with the release of 0.23 it isn't just sandbox only anymore. The career function is now live too, albeit under construction, but you can gather science points by doing experiments with which you can unlock newer parts etc.According to the devs update 0.24 will release contracts so you can become a sort of spacex company by launching satellites  into orbit for cash.When this game will be fully released it will be the most extensive space sim in it's class and can be fun for both casual players as for hardcore gamers who do their own calculations as to how much fuel they need and so on.One last thing: Did i mention mods?? KSP already has a really active modding community with tons of extra parts and fly ready spacecrafts. Also some of them add the capability of mining resources from other planets for that extra level of depth."
76561198054015901,Recommended,220200,9104209,"Posted: 14 February, 2014",all,hewench,"Overall Game Score 9/10Its hard to pull away from Kerbal for long enough to review it. Its that damn good. Even as an Alpha it is a very solid game. It runs stabilly with modest system requirments. For those that have yet to play it, kerbal space program is a space program simulator. You are tasked with looking towards the heavens and creating a vessel to get you there. From small probes to large interplanetary cruisors everything is at your fingertips with this games solid vehicle assembly building. It doesn't take very long to realize just how difficult it is to build a workable spaceship. The challenge and the joy of exploring the games solar system will have you blowing yourself up hundreds of times building the consistancy of launches, orbits and landings. I can't throw my money at this game fast enough.As a side note but an important one, I work at a public school in vermont that wished to use KSP for lessons in rocketry. I contacted the game developers and was surprised by how personable and great they were at meeting our needs. I'm sure they lost money on the many free subscriptions they gave us but it showed how great they were as people. Squad is a great company with a good business model, long story short they desearve your dollar in more ways than one."
