76561197970578211,Recommended,220200,8042360,"Posted: 14 December, 2013",all,Xenothor,"I think I can safely call Kerbal Space Program my favorite single player game of all time. There is a learning curve, as this is after all rocket science, but for me the learnig process was fun, and I've learned more about orbital mechanics and rocketry from playing this game then I would have ever thought. This game is not for everybody. There is nothing to shoot, there are no missions or goals, other than the ones you plan for yourself, and a significant time investment is required to accomplish anything significant, so more casual gamers should beware.In KSP you can design, build, and launch rockets, space probes, satelites, rovers, space stations, and space planes, in your efforts to explore the Kerbal solar system. Evey planet presents it own challenges, and failure will happen again and again, but when you are successful it's very rewarding, and every success will serve to inspire you toward planning missions of greater ambition. For me the failures were never frustrating, but just part of the fun. For anyone with an interest in simulations or space exploration, this game is a must!"
