76561198109612756,Recommended,220200,10894923,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,veryinky,"A fun game that teaches the basics of spaceflight.Core gameplay mechanics are assembling a spaceship out of available parts (crew pod, fuel tank, engine), piloting it to orbit and presumably either returning to the planet Kerbin or exploring distant moons or planets. Very useful for learning about the basics of orbital mechanics and the difficulties of space travel.Current version, 0.23.5 inclutes the framework of a ""career mode"" where the player has to perform science experiments to gain access to more advanced parts.One of the main draws to this game is the community modding support, where everything from cold war russian rocket engines to current private space enterprise to theoretical future science parts have been made. Mods also include gameplay changes such as mapping satellites, missions and contracts, communication networks and even functioning GPS satellites. If you want something changed in the game there's probably a mod for it.Game requires a lot of optimization and is not very stable on lower end computers or when running many mods. But then it's Early Access."
