76561197987724352,Recommended,220200,10805071,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,Ron Burgundy,"This game is excellent, though not for everyone. The game is challenging, and features realistic space flight and orbital mechanics. There is certainly a steep learning curve early on, but the difficulty makes the reward when you succeed that much greater. Beyond that, the game makes failure FUN! So don't think that you're going to get frustrated. If you have any interest in space flight, you will enjoy this game. The game will teach you about rocket science and the challenges of interplanetary travel.Build crazy rocket-powered contraptions, launch them into space, travel to moons and other planets throughout the system (an analog to the solar system). What's to dislike?Modes: there is currently a sandbox mode (all parts unlocked) and a Career mode (earn Science points by carrying out missions in order to unlock parts in the tech tree).The state of the game as it stands is very playable. There are some bugs, but it does not hinder the gameplay. The game is early access, so new content will be added in the future.Be warned: development is slow. However, SQUAD makes sure that each update is polished and robust before release, so the updates are worth the wait.Modability: there are TONS of mods for this game. Mods that add parts, mods that enhance the atmospherics, mods that turn the entire system in to the Solar System and scales it up to size, and more.TLDR: This game is loads of fun, even when your rockets are blowing up on the launchpad. Play sandbox and goof around with crazy contraptions, or play career for a fulfilling experience exploring, earning 'science' points and unlocking parts. Enjoy realistic orbital mechanics -- learn about real space flight!8.5/10"
