76561197982982266,Recommended,220200,8894887,"Posted: 28 January, 2014",all,Gerhardt Sploosh,"KSP represents the ultimate sandbox game for anyone that loved/loves space simulators. The learning curve is intense but reaching new personal achievments can be exhilirating. During your first few hours (especially if you play sandbox right away), you will gain a new appreciation for the science and engineering that goes into our real space program. Just don't go emailing NASA and telling them ""but it works in KSP"". The one downside of KSP is that it feels unfinished in many places. Career mode is just starting to unfold but lacks a few key elements to make it truly engaging. The pacing of the tech tree can be slow and will be almost completely unlocked before you leave Kerbin's sphere of influence if this is your first go around. I expect this will be less of a program when a rigorous budget system is implemented. On the plus side, the modding community and forums are full of some of the most creative and helpful people I've ever encountered in a videogame. Many of the games' shortcomings have been identified and someone has developed mods to improve them. From clouds, to aerodynamics, to realistic universe, to parts parts and more parts. Also, the mods are really easy to install. This is a game worth buying now and following until it's release and beyond."
