,Recommended,220200,15357528,"Posted: 14 April, 2015",all,Stupendous Man,"Having spent more than 60 hours in this game during the past few weeks, I think it's about time that I write a review for it.Some years ago I messed around with a space sim called 'Orbiter' and had a lot of fun with it. When Kerbal Space Program came out, I thought it looked like a dumbed down version of Orbiter and not really worth my time. Was I wrong!I just recently bought KSP at a sale, and immediately discovered that it was everything and so much more than Orbiter ever was. The basic spacecraft flying is the same, but KSP has added a lot more than was available in Orbiter: intuitive tools for orbit manoeuvers, buidling your own spacecraft, permanent bases, simple multistage rockets and now, a career mode.Sure, the solar system in KSP is simpler and more basic than the (real life) one in Orbiter, but the astrodynamics are the same if not as advanced (no orbital perturbations, all celestial bodies are spherical etc).What KSP does incredibly well is teach basic astrodynamics and rocket design. It may not be as advanced as in real life, but it teaches you the basics and gives a good idea of the challenges of launching interplanetary missions.EDIT: I originally complained about the aerodynamics being horrible, however, since version 1.0 that has been completely changed and is now quite good. /EDITApart from that, I can recommend this game 100%: not only is it great fun, but you'll learn a lot about real world space flight while exploring the unknown."
