,Recommended,220200,12474014,"Posted: 12 October, 2014",all,ups_guy,"If you love space, flight, and engineering, you'll love this game. If not, It's still extremely fun. It's not overly simplistic, or overly complicated. Being able to design and fly a ship that is capable of interpanetary travel while still able to return to earth is challenging, addicting, and satisfying. Finding the best way to complete objectives through individual trial and error is also very fun. Another huge plus is the fact that there is already a fairly large amount of content. I've so far only spent 42 hours with this title and have only safely made it to the ""mun"" and back a few times. Similar to programming, I save the designs that work best and trash or fix the ones that don't. Eventually, you'll have an arsenal of effective designs for specific categories of flight."
76561197980405855,Recommended,220200,8907645,"Posted: 29 January, 2014",all,Bosco007,"This game is not ""Rocket science"" neither is it ""Simple""With a steep learning curve I find it hard for those just starting up, but a few youtube videos and some reaserch on the wiki will help a lot, once you get out of kerbin's atmosphere your well on your way to reach the outer planets. Once you get down manuvers and the basics it becomes easier and yet challenging! Making it to the Mun is one thing, but landing a 6 man crew fully equiped with a rover and science lab is another. once you land on Mun (or minimus) the game will suck you in like a black hole! Say goodbye social life, and hello space command.Cons: Steep Learning Curve, quite a few bugs(Notice its in beta), and quite a few crashes when you build Massive(and I mean MASSIVE) Ships.Pros: Everything else + The mod comunity is HUGE theres so much to do, after 100 hours in I still havnt done all that their is to do, not even close.I reccomend everyone before purchase to do some research, watch some youtube tutorials and do some reading on the wiki, After that if you got the idea and the knowledge to give this game a go then purchase away! If your still confused and unsure about the complexity on fuel managing and air resistance, do more research or move along."
