,Recommended,220200,5479157,"Posted: 7 July, 2013",all,mysterybiscuit,"Kerbal Space Program is a game in Early Access made by Squad, a company that does not really have any experience with making games:The GoodFun, the game has a sandbox mode that is thoroughly enjoyable, you can put together whatever you want to do, as long as your computer (particulary your CPU) can cope with it.Realistic-ish, the game is in some points rather realistic, like the orbital mechanics. The aerodynamics are not really realistic, but it is still an exceptional amount of fun to have a perfectly normal plane pull of 15Gs. The game also shows you how it is to run a space program rather well, not that I have any experience running space program.Size, as many mothers say: ""Size does not matter!"" Well, if you are going to space, then you might want to have other planets at a far distance, so they can not affect you noticeably.Long, I have put 400 hours into this game and I have not yet been even close to seeing everything. I bet that you can put more hours in this game than Scott Manley and still not have seen everything.Time Warp, I am so glad that the time warp goes up to 100 000x, because otherwise missions to for example Jool (Jupiter) would take an eternity.Big modding community, the amount of mods that have come out for this game is big, nothing compared to Minecraft, but still it is amazing. For example the aerodynamic problem that I mentioned can be fixed with mods.The Mediocre:Difficult, the game is very difficult and the tutorials are not that amazing, but with help of youtubers like Scott Manley, you should be able to get into orbit within a few hours.Career mode, the career mode in this game is not really done yet and I did not really enjoy it, once the game is finished career mode might be a lot better, but in its current state.High Requirements, for this game to run properly, you will have to have a computer, particularly the CPU part that is rather high-end. I have no trouble with it, since I run an overclocked i7-4930k.The Bad:Kraken, even though the kraken has mostly been fixed, it is still there and sometimes really ruins the game. For example when you have finally grappled onto a massive asteroid, you start suffering from all kinds of glitches and these are very frustrating.The Verdict:This game is a good sandbox game and a rather good space simulator, but the aerodynamics are not the best but that can be fixed with mods. The only big bottleneck for you to buy this game is the high pc requirements, but as long as you have an i7 (tested on i7-870, i7-3630QM and i7-4930K) or a new i5 you should be able to run this game with more than 30FPS. This game is a good example of what new/indie companies can do."
