76561198117287352,Recommended,220200,22290059,"Posted: 7 April, 2016",all,SLC,"After playing this game for some time i kind of feel obliged to give a review.Kerbal Space Program, or short ""KSP"" starts you off with a space center. Mange it, build up your own space program. Of course you get tocrashfly your ships.I mainly play the ""Sandbox mode"". Here you don't have any restrictions on what (not) to do.In your space center you have two main buildings for building ships. The Vehicle Assembly Building (VAB) and the Space Plane Hangar (SPH).The SPH mainly is for planes and SSTOS, the VAB for rockets.You start your ship simple, command pod, fuel tank, engine. Maybe a parachute (optional).  After that you add what you think to be neccessary. This includes, but is not limited to, antennas, batteries, solar panels, landing gear, heatshields, wheels, wings. Make sure not to forget anything, you might get stuck in space.After building your ship, the fun really starts. You get to go to space! Go you!Just to realise that going up is not enough. Start over.Go sideways.Run out of fuel.Start over.Repeat. Until you get to orbit.By now you have probably realised that your knowledge might not be enough, so start looking up tutorials. Try to recreate them and reacht the Moon (Mun in KSP).After a lot of time, planning and trial and error you manage tocrashland your ship on the mun.I will have a hard time describing it, but the feeling is amazing.I know this review is by no means perfect. I don't think it does KSP justice. People have writtenessays on the most basic things.If you are interrested in space, flight, planes, tinkering and a ""few"" explosions here and there, get this game.Just be aware that this game is very heavy on physics and (rocket) science. And a bit of math (not too much tho)."
