,Recommended,220200,7898913,"Posted: 3 December, 2013",all,Kodiak-K2,"I would HIGHLY recomend this game. It is regularly on sale so pick it up then but man.... this game... To give you some forewarning, there is a STEEP learning curve in this game but if you go to YouTube and look up Scot Manley he has extremly informative videos on how to get you going in this game. You will crash, a lot. You will loose ships due to lack of fuel, a lot. But when you make it to that destination, and you will (eventually) it will be one a moment you will remember forever. I would recommend playing through the campaign instead of sandbox purely for the fact that it will help train you in some flight mechanics. You won't be able to build a craft that will hit the Mun (their equivalent to a moon) but it will still be a lot of fun. My review didn't convince you? Go over to YouTube and type in KSP Build Fly Dream Trailer. That should be a good litmus test to whether or not you want to play this game."
