,Recommended,220200,11799972,"Posted: 20 August, 2014",all,LiquidSolidus,"Once you get a hang of its basics, you'll find yourself spiraling into chaotic machine after chaotic machine until you finally build the space rocket of your dreams. You'll feel like Thomas Edison, having dozens of rockets blow up immediately, barely make it out of the atmosphere, or get lost in space due to lack of fuel. But these failures are always learning experiences, and once you finally get what you're after, the achievement builds and builds. Getting out of the atmosphere and landing on Kerbal's Mars equivalent, Duna, differ vastly in skill required to pull off, but both yield an unbelievable sense of ""I did it!"" The game's still in development, and the career mode is a bit lacking, but the sandbox will net hundreds of hours for casual astronomers and brave explorers alike."
