,Recommended,220200,2341294,"Posted: 2 April, 2013",all,TwistedLogic,"A strangely detailed* and entertaining building/space travel sim that does everything you might expect but, unexpectedly, does many of them in the way we wish other games had done them in the first place. The construction of spaceships is not the idle snapping of pieces into place to make your creation simply 'look good' and perform the same, every single piece you create has an effect on the ships performance. Every piece has a use, a function and often some kind of activation to give your ship everything it needs to do it's job. What is it's job? That depends on you. Get something into a stable orbit around the planet, make a crazy-looking land rover, land on the Mun (Moon) and even construct and launch a space-station to go anywhere you want, even distant planets. Each part of this game is fleshed out and feels complete, despite it being an early alpha. A fun game to mess around in if you can't quite get your head around the learning curve (which is pretty steep atm) but the payoff for achieving something you set out to do is fantastic and can take hours from your day.Recommendation: Play the demo, if you have fun, get the full thing. The demo has alot of content in there, so you can have an awesome time with just that if you don't want to shell out for the full version just yet. Still, definitely worth a look."
