76561198007995521,Recommended,220200,11351794,"Posted: 21 July, 2014",all,ZappBrannigan,"This game holds my personal record for most hours played. It keeps drawing you back in. Even in sandbox mode you feel what it was like in the real space program, learning to build a stable ship, learning how to orbit, learning to dock, and finally standing on another world. The new career path has made this even more noticable. The physics are outstanding and are what you would expect from a advanced flight sim. The freedom to build in sandbox mode, and spending hours trying to land on the Mun, then actually pulling it off is a great feeling, even for a video game.The only real feature missing is mission planning. There are addons and mods that help you plan your missions, but I feel that should be part of the game. You shoudl not have to speed up time and wait for Mars to be in the right position for landing. Nor should you have to create your manuevers on the fly. I think a real mission control woul be worth while. An ability to know when to launch, know when to manuever ahead of time, that would really make the sim come alive.Other than that 10/10 for me personally. One of my favorite games to have come out in the last few years, and one that keeps finding ways to bring me back."
