76561197994712579,Recommended,220200,8413316,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,Can you actually just not feed,Yes.
,Recommended,220200,10734545,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,Monofraps,"Kerbal Space Program is all about, well, your own space program.It is an increadibly fun game. If building impossible space crafts, shooting them into space and killing innocent Kerbals is your thing, I can definitely recommend this game.The base game lacks some performance here and some features there. However, the latter can easily be fixed by installing mods which add a lot to the game - not only parts but also actual game play mechanics.The graphics are *fine* for this sort of game. Don't expect AAA-like super realistic textures, though.As mentioned before, KSP does have some slight performance issues. Don't get me wrong here, the frame rate is definitely at an acceptable level. However, the more crafts you have near you in space the longer physics calculations seem to take which will lead to some degree of lag eventually. Talking about physics, *do not expect super-realistic physics*. KSP is based on Unity which is a great engine for casual-ish games but its physics simulation sucks. I think I read an article stating that Squad had to heavily modify Unity's physics engine in order to make KSP possible. - From my observations: orbital physics seem totally fine but your creation tends to start wobbling without reason from time to time."
