76561198053571214,Recommended,220200,8802621,"Posted: 21 January, 2014",all,NANDálf,"A really good game by indie developer Squad. As I'm typing this, the game is still in alpha, yet it is already capable of hours of time consumption. With a healthy modding community, unique challenges, amusing part descriptions, and a vast solar system to explore, this sandbox space sim is a great way to kill a few hours. And Kerbals. Inadvertently. For the most part.A word of warning, however: this game is not for the impatient. It is very time consuming (but rewarding), and can be very challenging, especially early on. For anyone new to the game, I'd recommend going on YouTube and watching a few of Scott Manley's video tutorials, and a few of his regular videos (especially for some good mods). There's nothing more frustrating than when you crash into that space station you were building in low Kerbin orbit because you didn't realise that in order to perform a safe docking, you must completely match orbits and velocity."
