,Recommended,220200,33192428,Posted: 3 July,all,MidnightSpecial,"This has to be one of my all time favorite games ever made.   I started stalling out on the game because I just wasn't very good at giving myself challenges so I decided to use the custom difficulty settings to make my own game mode.  Give yourself a ton of starting funds and science, jack up the science rewards, and basically just get to play Sandbox mode, but still have access to the contracts that constantly give you specific tasks to shoot for.  Also, the modding community around this game is second to none.  Everything from life support mods (awesome) to quality of life tweaks are readily available and are usually very well maintained.  I can't wait to see where this game goes from here, but I've got plans to spend hundreds more hours in KSP."
